<h1>Login to Libraries.io</h1>

<p>Please click on one of the buttons below to link your account.</p>

<p>
  <%= link_to '/auth/github', class: 'btn btn-primary' do %>
    <%= fa_icon 'github' %> Login with GitHub
  <% end %>
</p>

<p>
  <%= link_to '/auth/gitlab', class: 'btn btn-primary' do %>
    <%= fa_icon 'gitlab' %> Login with GitLab
  <% end %>
</p>

<p>
  <%= link_to '/auth/bitbucket', class: 'btn btn-primary' do %>
    <%= fa_icon 'bitbucket' %> Login with Bitbucket
  <% end %>
</p>

<p>By logging in you accept our <a href='/terms'>terms of service</a> and <a href='/privacy'>privacy policy</a>.</p>
<hr>
<h2>Why login to Libraries.io?</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Libraries.io lets you watch packages that you depend on and notifies you when there's a new release. When you follow a package, new releases will show up here in your newsfeed.</li>
  <li>Data from Libraries.io can easily be integrated into your day-to-day workflows using <a href="/api">our API</a>. Get your API key now!</li>
  <li>Libraries.io can email you about new versions of your dependencies</li>
</ul>